---
description: AdapterOS repo rules (defer to AGENTS.md)
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow `AGENTS.md` for canonical repo invariants and workflows. If anything here conflicts, `AGENTS.md` wins.

- Existing code first; minimal diffs; avoid refactors unless explicitly requested.
- Runtime/persistent paths: use `./var/` (gitignored). Never use `/tmp`, `/private/tmp`, `/var/tmp`.
- Never create `var/` or `tmp/` directories inside crates.
- Before running expensive actions (full-workspace tests, `cargo clean`, starting services, downloading models), ask or justify.
- UI work: use `AOS_DEV_NO_AUTH=1 ./start` to bypass RBAC; do not modify auth/RBAC to unblock UI.
